lgp.core.evolution

Class ResultAggregators.InMemoryResultAggregator<T>

  • ResultAggregator
    • lgp.core.evolution.ResultAggregators.InMemoryResultAggregator<T>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Module
    Enclosing class:
    ResultAggregators

    public static class ResultAggregators.InMemoryResultAggregator<T>
extends ResultAggregator

    A simple result aggregator that builds an internal collection of results.

    Care must be taken with this aggregator, as it will keep all results in memory and only relieve results once cleared. Results should either be exported regularly or the number of results aggregated should be limited. Alternatively, another aggregator that flushes results automatically could be used.

    Note that if using this implementation in a multi-threaded environment, there is no guarantee about the order of the results produced. The built-in class Trainers which contain result aggregation logic ensure that results are grouped per-run, but there it is not certain that the runs will be in order.

    See Also:
    class Trainers
